What happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?
It is like allocating new space to books on a bookshelf. Sets you up for better organization later when needed

How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository?
What value do you think it offers?
It is like an intermediate place like Add to cart in a shopping site. Where things are temporarily saved. It helps you decide how much you want to commit one by one. Otherwise, we will be forced to make big commits which include the status of all files even if only one file had a change. 

